{
  "texts": [
    "In the DIL setting, only one domain data can be accessed by the learning model at one time.",
    "Additionally, data from previously visited domains cannot be used again when the model is training on the following domains.",
    "Formally, the learning model M begins training on D 1 and progressively learns D 2,..., D 𝑆.",
    "The crucial challenge in DIL is to ensure that under D 𝑆, the model M can still maintain the performance on D 1,..., D 𝑆 -1.",
    "The motivation of this research is to enhance the accuracy of tasks across all domains in this learning paradigm."
  ]
}